HEADWORD: Pickaninny
<hw>Pick"a*nin`ny</hw> <pr>(p⟦icr⟧k"⟦adot⟧*n⟦icr⟧n`n⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Pickaninnies</plw>
<pr>(p⟦icr⟧k"⟦adot⟧*n⟦icr⟧n`n⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. Sp.
<ets>peque⟦ntil⟧o</ets> little, young.]</ety> <def>A small child;
especially, a negro or mulatto infant. Now (2001) used primarily in the
latter sense, and in that sense often considered derogatory.</def>
